news.title: Sunac China faces winding-up petition in Hong Kong
news.para: The firm is working to restructure its offshore debt after missing some bond payments earlier this year, adding to a wave of defaults in China's debt-laden property sector.

news.title: China state firms takeover Evergrande's $1.1 billion holding in Shengjing Bank
news.para: In July, Evergrande, the world's most indebted property developer, said its unit, Evergrande Nanchang, had been ordered to pay an unamed guarantor 7.3 billion yuan for failing to honour debt obligations.

news.title: Goa: Construction sector struggles for sand, looks at alternatives
news.para: ​At the same time, it has compelled builders to look at cheaper and more accessible alternatives such as readymade cement bricks, gypsum, manufactured sand and even cement-less concrete.

news.title: Sebi extends auction date to September 20 for Golden Life Agro properties
news.para: The regulator will auction two properties of the company for a reserve price totalling Rs 8 crore. The properties put on the block are a plot and a double-storied building located in West Bengal.

news.title: Gujarat: Registrar officials told to clear all property papers in 30 days
news.para: The order states that the applicant should be informed via three notices if any clarification required. The reasons for the pendency has to be entered on an online intranet platform of the revenue department.

news.title: Maharashtra starts property e-registrations, to also introduce blockchain
news.para: With this, Maharashtra has become the first state to enable e-registrations of properties. Initially the facilty will be enabled for e-registration of agreement of first sale and resale transactions will not be part of it.

news.title: RLDA invites bids for leasing out 29,065 sq meter land parcel in Sirsa
news.para: The proposed land parcel is located near the railway colony and will be leased out for 99 years. The reserve price of the land is approximately Rs 28.47 crore.

news.title: Max Estates agrees to buy Acreage Builders for Rs 322 crore enterprise value
news.para: MaxVIL, which is part of Max Group, plans to develop a commercial project with a leasable area of 1.6 million square feet on this land parcel, marking its entry into Gurugram real estate market. It already has a presence in Noida and Delhi property markets.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Housing scheme beneficiaries breach terms for personal use
news.para: The civic body council that recently met considered an issue where one beneficiary of a housing scheme apparently sold the land purchased under the housing scheme to raise money for the marriage of his daughter.

news.title: Kolhapur's development plan delayed over lack of GIS mapping agency
news.para: As per section 38 of Maharashtra Regional Town Planning Act, the development plans of the cities should be revised once in 20 years so that the demands of the growing population can be met properly.

news.title: Coimbatore: Registered engineers to be held responsible for building violations
news.para: In an online meeting organized by the city corporation on Monday, executive engineer (planning) K Karupathal warned that registered engineers would face action if there were any violations found in the building construction.

news.title: Nagpur civic body to auction 6,925 open plots to recover Rs 37.4 crore tax dues
news.para: Deputy municipal commissioner (revenue) Milind Meshram said around 75,596 plot owners across the city have been defaulting on property tax for years. The outstanding arrears from these open plot owners is around Rs 284 crore.

news.title: Chandigarh: Only three of 99 leasehold properties sold in e-auction
news.para: The poor response to the leasehold properties on offer is despite the CHB reducing the reserve price by about 15% in comparison to the last e-tender for these units.

news.title: Nashik civic body brings 3,000 new properties under tax net in two months
news.para: As per the norms, it is mandatory for the builders to obtain building completion certificates (BCCs) from the civic body after the completion of the buildings.

news.title: Robust demand for engineering infrastructure from Southeast Asia: Bridging the business & engineering gap via this SME
news.para: Ishan International has been a certified star export house recognized by EEPC for the past 26 years due to its 80% market share in the Southeast Asian market.
